uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.inputs

Class ErrorInput<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.inputs.ErrorInput<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of input
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Input<T>, UnmodifiableInput

    public class ErrorInput<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements UnmodifiableInput, Input<T>
    An ErrorInput is an unmodifiable input that never validates. It can used to indicate that no valid selections are possible for the user or that an error occurred while generating the form.
